technical_knowledge.q11_bloc_bug:
The issue is that state doesn’t update immediately after emit. So when you call emit(state + 1) twice, both emissions use the old state, not the incremented one.

Fix: calculate the new state yourself or emit the final value directly:

emit(state + 2); // adds 2 at once

Or, if we want sequential updates:

final newState = state + 1;
emit(newState);
emit(newState + 1);

 in BLoC, state only updates after the handler finishes
